cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the use of positive definite kernels in machine learning, which is a topic commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of set theory and intersection in the proposed earth mover's intersection (EMI) also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the evaluation of kernels in various computer vision tasks suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
